# Budget Pet — Project Context

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|-------|------|
| Backend | Python 3.11, FastAPI, Uvicorn |
| Frontend | Next.js 15, React 19, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS 4, TanStack Query |
| Bot | python-telegram-bot 22 |
| DB | PostgreSQL on Railway (`psycopg2` legacy + `asyncpg` finance/plaid) |
| Hosting | Railway (3 services: FastAPI, Next.js, telegram bot) |

## Key Conventions

- **Two DB drivers** — `web/postgres_db.py` (psycopg2, sync) for legacy routes; `web/finance/repo.py` and `web/plaid/repo.py` (asyncpg, async) for finance/plaid. Never mix them.
- **Auth** — Sessions in memory. `/api/*` protected by `AuthMiddleware` (cookie or `Authorization: Bearer`). Legacy routes `/expenses`, `/limits`, `/report` are intentionally unprotected (bot compatibility).
- **`expenses.source`** — `manual` | `plaid` | `plaid_sandbox`. Rows with `plaid_sandbox` are excluded from all reports and statistics.
- **Every new feature** — separate module, not inside large existing files.
- **Docs are source of truth** — always check `docs/` before implementing. Key files: `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/api.md`, `docs/plaid.md`, `docs/bot.md`.

## Repo Structure

```
budget_pet/
├── web/            # FastAPI app (main.py, auth/, finance/, plaid/)
├── services/       # Shared adapters (bot_adapter, finance_adapter, search_filter)
├── frontend/src/   # Next.js (app/, components/, lib/, types/)
├── bot.py          # Telegram bot entry point
├── tests/          # pytest
└── docs/           # Full documentation in Russian
```

## Plaid Integration

- Products: `transactions` + `liabilities`
- Expenses synced to `expenses` table with full metadata (merchant_name, plaid_category_raw, plaid_pfc_category, is_pending)
- Income (amount < 0) synced to `finance_income` with `person='Plaid'`
- Liabilities sync updates APR, min_payment, due_day on credit cards and loans
